Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.52,0:00:05.27,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,What is this, my lord?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.44,0:00:07.65,Green HUD,,0000,0000,0000,,Evans /Person of the Land      Pursall /Person of the Land
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.94,0:00:07.61,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,They're all People of the Land.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.65,0:00:08.48,Green HUD,,0000,0000,0000,,Jessica /Person of the Land                 Belna /Person of the Land
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.02,0:00:10.15,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Sleeping?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.53,0:00:11.99,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,They're all asleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.70,0:00:13.78,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.20,0:00:15.53,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.53,0:00:18.78,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Sh-Shining wings...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.79,0:00:21.83,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Shining wings?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.55,0:01:59.09,Location,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(406,1)\an9}Guild Hall/ Cafeteria B\N{\fs18}Japan Server\NAkihabara\NCity/ No Monsters\NNo PVP \NEntry Restrictions/ None \NExit Restrictions/ None
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.71,0:01:59.09,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The fifty-four People of the Land who fell \Nasleep are being kept at the guild hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.09,0:02:01.35,Default,Ri,0000,0000,0000,,The same phenomenon occurred in Maihama.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.35,0:02:04.06,Default,Ri,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Sergiatte is still asleep and won't wake up.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.14,0:02:07.98,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Silver Sword says Susukino is safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.27,0:02:11.15,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Then only People of the Land fall asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.56,0:02:12.61,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.02,0:02:16.69,Green HUD,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(194,304)}Belna /Person of the Land
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.61,0:02:17.03,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Their MP falls to zero and doesn't \Nrecover fast enough naturally.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.69,0:02:19.66,Green HUD,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fs26\fad(279,1)}Belna /Person of the Land
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.03,0:02:19.66,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So their MP is being continually drained?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.28,0:02:26.12,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Eyewitnesses suggest it's due to a \Nmoth-like monster with shining wings.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.12,0:02:28.41,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,A moth spirit, probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.79,0:02:32.67,Default,Ri,0000,0000,0000,,There wasn't any monster like that in the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.59,0:02:35.96,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,For now, it appears our best move
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.96,0:02:38.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is to keep investigating and \Nto strengthen our defenses.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.13,0:02:39.88,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What about Shibuya?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.88,0:02:40.97,Default,So,0000,0000,0000,,Shibuya?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.47,0:02:44.35,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Regan told us that the remains of the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.35,0:02:46.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,broadcasting station in Shibuya \Nmay still be functional.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.35,0:02:49.39,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Shouldn't we investigate that immediately?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.89,0:02:52.15,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And ignore the moth spirit?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.69,0:02:57.11,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It may seem cold, but if only People \Nof the Land are falling asleep—
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.11,0:02:58.15,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.53,0:03:01.99,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's just how much stress the \Nadventurers are under right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.24,0:03:04.70,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The Royal Guard's rampage.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.70,0:03:06.33,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The flavor text coming true.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.33,0:03:07.87,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And now this...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.75,0:03:11.33,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And there are signs of impending \Nwar with People of the Land.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.96,0:03:14.50,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have the energy to \Nspend on anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.50,0:03:19.01,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I do understand how you feel, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.01,0:03:24.01,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Even if we can go home, \Nit's not going to happen right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.01,0:03:25.60,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Shiroe?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.60,0:03:27.01,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.14,0:03:31.35,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,But that doesn't mean we can do nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.89,0:03:33.98,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Let's keep an eye on the situation \Nand see what we can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.65,0:03:41.53,Title,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1407,1)}Sleep of the Eternal Moth
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.07,0:03:39.44,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Sleep of the Eternal Moth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.28,0:03:44.11,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,There aren't many people today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.70,0:03:46.91,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, with the moth spirit running around...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.04,0:03:57.29,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.29,0:03:58.88,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,What did Chief Nyanta say?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.25,0:04:03.34,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,He's going to patrol with us tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.63,0:04:04.51,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.93,0:04:09.93,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,The People of the Land who fell asleep \Nshow no signs of waking up yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.27,0:04:11.35,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I'm worried about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.27,0:04:14.85,Default - flashback,T,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going home.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.94,0:04:23.36,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Are you thinking about your home?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.53,0:04:24.61,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Rudy?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.91,0:04:30.62,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we're apart, I don't think \Nour relationship will change.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.33,0:04:34.12,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I might not be able to see you anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.54,0:04:38.13,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, if you have a place \Nto go home to, you should.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.71,0:04:43.30,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,There are some people who can't, \Neven if they want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.72,0:04:45.76,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Rudy...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.06,0:04:52.85,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, we're going to head out on patrol.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.85,0:04:53.64,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.85,0:04:56.56,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Chief, take care of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.56,0:04:57.31,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Shiro!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.19,0:04:59.44,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe! Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.73,0:05:01.23,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,They're here! They're here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.23,0:05:02.48,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,A whole swarm of moths!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.36,0:05:06.57,Monsters,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(193,182)}Eternal Moth
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.86,0:05:05.74,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Eternal moths?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.62,0:05:11.83,Default,So,0000,0000,0000,,So many of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.29,0:05:13.54,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.00,0:05:16.04,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Could this be...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.13,0:05:20.92,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I hate bugs!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.84,0:05:30.30,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.06,0:05:34.48,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The shed scales are passing through \Nthe city's defense magic?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.48,0:05:35.89,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Just draw their attention!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.89,0:05:37.73,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Push them outside the walls!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.06,0:05:40.73,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The southwest side's about to be breached...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.73,0:05:42.44,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Team 2, cover them!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.44,0:05:43.48,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.65,0:05:46.49,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you have to go to your wife, Demi?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.20,0:05:50.24,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm having her lead People of the Land to safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.24,0:05:54.75,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let a single one of them into our town!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.04,0:05:59.17,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,All the Royal Guards fell asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.17,0:06:00.63,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That was unexpected.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.04,0:06:03.59,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,An attack from outside the zone...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.13,0:06:06.05,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Get the People of the Land to safety!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.05,0:06:06.92,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.92,0:06:08.88,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,This is going to be bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.43,0:06:11.26,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Marielle, there are more here!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.26,0:06:12.85,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.05,0:06:14.89,HUD1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs18}Bibiko /Adventurer     Tarosa /Adventurer\N\NJuggler /Adventurer     Stacy /Adventurer
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.14,0:06:14.97,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Even adventurers?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.14,0:06:17.23,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't only People of the Land?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.23,0:06:18.98,Default,So,0000,0000,0000,,It's dangerous to be outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.98,0:06:22.40,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, get inside the guild building!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.19,0:06:30.16,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,At last, adventurers have also started to fall, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.66,0:06:35.16,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that if shed scales get \Non you, you fall asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.49,0:06:40.08,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It may be that your Psyche, your MP, \Nis drained from your body.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.08,0:06:39.96,HUD1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(315,312)}Psyche
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.08,0:06:42.67,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps we should call it "Missing Psyche Disease."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.08,0:06:42.67,HUD1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(320,1)}Missing Psyche Disease
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.67,0:06:45.55,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,But some people are fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.55,0:06:50.68,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know the difference between those \Nwho fall asleep and those who don't, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.68,0:06:52.68,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You don't die, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.01,0:06:53.68,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.18,0:06:57.22,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If you die, you can revive at the Cathedral.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.64,0:07:00.69,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But once you fall asleep...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.27,0:07:02.27,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,How did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.27,0:07:05.44,Default,So,0000,0000,0000,,I've found the eternal moths' nest, Shiro.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.86,0:07:07.94,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Where is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.65,0:07:11.41,Location,So,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(402,1)\fs20\an9}Town of Shibuya\N{\fs18}Japan Server\NShibuya\NCity/ Monsters Present\NPVP Permitted\NSkill Use Permitted\NEntry Restrictions/ None\NExit Restrictions/ None
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.94,0:07:09.03,Default,So,0000,0000,0000,,In Shibuya.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.74,0:07:11.03,Default,So,0000,0000,0000,,It's really bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.91,0:07:14.91,Default,So,0000,0000,0000,,The player town of Shibuya \Nhas turned into a dungeon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.37,0:07:17.41,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,And where is the moths' nest?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.41,0:07:19.46,Default,So,0000,0000,0000,,In the remains of the Shibuya broadcast building.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.46,0:07:21.54,Default,So,0000,0000,0000,,It's a raid zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.00,0:07:25.54,Default,So,0000,0000,0000,,Its new name is the "Calling Fortress."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.75,0:07:25.92,Location,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(358,1)\an9}Calling Fortress\N{\fs18}Japan Server\NShibuya\NDungeon/ Monsters Present\NPVP Permitted\NSkill Use Permitted\NEntry Restrictions/ None\NExit Restrictions/ None
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.67,0:07:29.42,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.42,0:07:33.14,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's a prototype based on the \Ngame's capture functions.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.14,0:07:37.68,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But if you use it for more than \Nten minutes, it explodes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.52,0:07:40.68,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Until last week, it was completely normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.68,0:07:44.19,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It seems there's a seal on the entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.56,0:07:47.94,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Is it possible that monster eggs \Nor an eternal moth cocoon fell
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.94,0:07:52.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from the moon and was drawn by \Nthat device you call an antenna?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.82,0:07:54.70,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,From the moon in the sky?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.20,0:07:58.37,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,On the moon is a community of Observers
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.37,0:08:00.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,whom we're trying to contact.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.83,0:08:04.21,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And the monsters called "Geniuses" \Nwere there, as well, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.71,0:08:08.96,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,So are those eternal moths a type of Genius?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.96,0:08:11.01,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Then why would they want everyone's MP?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.63,0:08:14.72,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Roe 2's letter did say that the Geniuses
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.72,0:08:17.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are collecting something they called "empathions."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.35,0:08:20.52,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't understand what they were, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.43,0:08:23.56,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Is it MP?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.06,0:08:25.98,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,That's highly likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.98,0:08:29.69,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The eternal moths appeared at the same \Ntime yesterday and the day before.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.15,0:08:32.49,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The same time the moon rises.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.90,0:08:35.86,Default,18,0000,0000,0000,,18:22, precisely.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.86,0:08:39.70,Default,18,0000,0000,0000,,A third wave is certain to come tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.04,0:08:43.71,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,The first time, it was People of the Land, \Nand the second, it was adventurers, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.04,0:08:45.96,Default,So,0000,0000,0000,,Their numbers are increasing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.96,0:08:50.34,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,To prevent damages, we'll probably \Nhave to destroy the antenna.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.55,0:08:53.34,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But that's the only thing in Yamato that...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.34,0:08:54.80,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.80,0:08:56.43,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,And according to legend,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.43,0:09:00.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,an antenna is necessary for \Ncommunication with the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.85,0:09:05.73,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,If we destroy it, Shiroe's plan may \Nbe impossible to execute.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.73,0:09:07.15,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.44,0:09:09.02,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,What about the other servers?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.02,0:09:10.15,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.82,0:09:14.19,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We have barely any information \Non the foreign servers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.61,0:09:19.24,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Even if the facilities do exist somewhere \Nelse, they may be nonfunctional.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.24,0:09:20.87,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But if we don't do something,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.87,0:09:24.20,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,we'll have even bigger problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.50,0:09:27.00,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we'll just have to give up this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.29,0:09:31.75,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So what do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.55,0:09:34.59,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The Calling Fortress is a raid zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.05,0:09:36.93,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it appears to be in front of us,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.93,0:09:39.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's impossible to attack from the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.76,0:09:43.89,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We'll need to go inside from the main \Nentrance, and head for the goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.48,0:09:47.52,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We'll dispatch a raid team immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.69,0:09:53.53,HUD1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(397,1)\fs20}Shiroe      Naotsugu      Tetra \NParty 1     Akatsuki     Marielle     Kushiyatama
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.53,0:09:55.57,HUD1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs20}Party 2     Serara     Nyanta     Nazuna
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.57,0:09:58.28,HUD1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs20}Soujirou     Korou     Henrietta
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.28,0:10:03.04,HUD1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs20}Party 3     Fragrant Olive    Richou     Rieze \NTohya     Minori      Yuzuko
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.04,0:10:04.41,HUD1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs20}Party 4      Rundel Haus Code     Isuzu     Hien
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.41,0:10:07.79,HUD1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs20}Shouryuu     Isami     Kurinon
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.00,0:10:10.71,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Some of them don't have very high levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.71,0:10:14.30,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I selected them from people who didn't fall \Nasleep when exposed to the moths' scales.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.84,0:10:19.05,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, there's no guarantee \Nthey'll withstand the next attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.18,0:10:22.55,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You don't want to investigate the fortress first?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.89,0:10:24.31,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,There's no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.31,0:10:27.06,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So we're taking a gamble, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.14,0:10:30.10,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to keep you waiting!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.81,0:10:32.48,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,You're coming, too, old man?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.48,0:10:38.78,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Apparently, there's a special seal \Non the Calling Fortress's entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.78,0:10:42.20,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe asked me to release it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.45,0:10:44.20,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,That's not the only reason, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.45,0:10:48.46,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,This situation is a first in the world's history.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.08,0:10:51.71,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,As the bearer of the Miral Lake name,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.71,0:10:54.29,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I have a responsibility to see it through.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.29,0:10:58.67,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,We may not be able to protect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.67,0:11:01.01,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.01,0:11:03.72,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take care of myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.64,0:11:07.47,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Facilities across Yamato have been knocked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.06,0:11:10.23,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard what's happening in Shibuya, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.73,0:11:15.19,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I shall see what decision you adventurers make.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.98,0:11:17.90,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Take care of Akihabara for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.32,0:11:20.15,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You take care, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.86,0:11:21.91,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Einz...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.91,0:11:22.49,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.12,0:11:24.37,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'll believe
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.37,0:11:26.54,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,that you're a member of the Round Table, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.21,0:11:34.75,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Our target is the raid zone deep in the \NShibuya Dungeon, the Calling Fortress.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.38,0:11:38.76,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,We will destroy the antenna there to stop \Nthe spread of the eternal moths,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.34,0:11:40.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then wipe them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.93,0:11:50.48,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Let's finish this by moonrise!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.49,0:12:03.11,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,There are six hours until moonrise.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.62,0:12:07.28,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Eight moon rabbits from the old Dougenzaka area.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.62,0:12:08.74,Monsters,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Moon Rabbit
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.28,0:12:09.37,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Average level 91!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.37,0:12:11.79,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Keep pressure on them while heading \Ntoward Old Center Street.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.79,0:12:15.33,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Six rabbits from two o'clock, \Nand six from ten o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.67,0:12:17.13,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,This is just so strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.42,0:12:21.30,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,This happens right when we start thinking \Nabout communicating with the moon?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.30,0:12:22.17,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Shiro!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.17,0:12:23.38,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,From ahead of us, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.38,0:12:24.30,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Nine more!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.09,0:12:27.18,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Party 2, draw them to the front.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.93,0:12:30.31,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Party 1, front line, head to the front and...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.31,0:12:32.69,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,No, split the group to the rear!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.90,0:12:37.77,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Richou and Tohya, support group 1!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.77,0:12:38.82,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.82,0:12:41.69,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Yuzuko, Olive, support each party.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.15,0:12:44.32,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Forward, group 4, secure a path!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.32,0:12:45.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.28,0:12:46.99,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Minori, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.99,0:12:48.74,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,She's so cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.74,0:12:51.95,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It's called "Abbreviated Full-Power \NControlled Combat."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.95,0:12:53.96,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,She learned it directly from Shiroe!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.96,0:12:56.38,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,There are just too many!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.38,0:12:57.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.63,0:12:59.75,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I'll heal you, Naotsugu.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.67,0:13:04.68,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Tetra's healing will work \Nbetter than hers, Naotsugu!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.68,0:13:07.55,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,If they know what we're doing, \Nthis is exactly what they want.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.55,0:13:09.01,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Olive, get back!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.22,0:13:11.68,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,No, cover Richou from the right!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.52,0:13:13.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoops...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.23,0:13:14.18,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.18,0:13:15.89,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.89,0:13:16.81,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.81,0:13:18.02,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,More enemies!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.02,0:13:19.90,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,New enemies incoming from eight o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.90,0:13:21.19,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Sh-Shiroe!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.19,0:13:22.44,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,A minotaur!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.44,0:13:23.90,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,That's a surprise I'm not at all happy about!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.90,0:13:26.03,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,This is an ambush!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.32,0:13:28.24,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,You're kidding me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.57,0:13:32.20,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,We may really lose our hope to get home.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.20,0:13:33.29,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.29,0:13:35.16,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Two minotaurs!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.16,0:13:36.08,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Your orders!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.75,0:13:40.42,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Center around parties 2 and 4 \Nand break through Old Spain-zaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.42,0:13:42.34,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, there... Take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.34,0:13:43.42,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Nyanta...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.76,0:13:46.55,Default,Ri,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, they're all monsters I've never seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.55,0:13:48.47,Default,Ri,0000,0000,0000,,This is very interesting...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.01,0:13:52.39,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Watch out, old guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.18,0:13:55.81,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Party 1, fall back and focus on healing!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.52,0:14:01.57,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,But we can't abandon this world, \Nor the People of the Land, to this state.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.82,0:14:03.90,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Maintain formation and keep going forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.90,0:14:06.32,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,No, right at the next corner!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.45,0:14:08.20,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,This is a mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.20,0:14:09.99,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't like him...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.99,0:14:12.45,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't have time to investigate in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.45,0:14:13.95,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.95,0:14:14.83,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.25,0:14:16.58,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,This is pathetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.04,0:14:20.79,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,My lord respects him as the \NTea Party's famous strategist.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.79,0:14:23.25,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I wondered how good he was...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.55,0:14:28.97,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,This is the Calling Fortress.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.43,0:14:31.47,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Four hours and seven minutes left.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.76,0:14:34.47,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,This is a complicated seal...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.81,0:14:36.77,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.18,0:14:38.94,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Nice panties!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.94,0:14:41.44,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Way to go, skeleton-guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.44,0:14:43.48,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I know. I'm awesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.86,0:14:44.73,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.73,0:14:45.73,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.36,0:14:50.07,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Our phantom-beast scouts have \Ngiven us some information,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.07,0:14:53.99,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,but as we head for the top, \Nwe'll confirm the situation on each floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.49,0:14:58.54,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Each party's back ranks will keep their distance, \Nto prepare for the unexpected.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.42,0:15:01.50,Default - italics,So,0000,0000,0000,,Votive Sword Kogarasumaru!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.13,0:15:07.26,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Man, I can't see Sou...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.26,0:15:09.26,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,More enemies! Six rabbits!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.26,0:15:11.89,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let the captain be the only one to fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.59,0:15:14.35,Default - italics,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Samurai's Challenge!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.35,0:15:17.43,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Fighting girls are so great...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.43,0:15:19.10,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,The shining sweat!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.10,0:15:21.19,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,The West Wind gets along well, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.56,0:15:23.69,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,We're partners. Of course we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.73,0:15:26.44,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I love it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.78,0:15:28.11,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.86,0:15:29.90,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.90,0:15:30.70,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.70,0:15:31.95,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.36,0:15:34.58,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,All these corridors look the same...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.58,0:15:36.70,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,It's literally a labyrinth!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.70,0:15:38.20,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,A dead end?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.20,0:15:39.83,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's sealed with cocoons!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.08,0:15:41.87,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Same over here, my lord!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.87,0:15:43.58,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I can't see past it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.62,0:15:43.58,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.92,0:15:46.09,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,The west corridor is overflowing with moon rabbits!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.21,0:15:51.47,HUD1,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs20}Fragrant Olive     Nazuna     Kurinon \NMinori     Yuzuko
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.80,0:15:50.13,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,The way we're running through \NMP could prove fatal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.13,0:15:50.97,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.01,0:15:53.47,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,We'll head back down for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.30,0:15:56.85,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,After coming this far?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.85,0:15:57.85,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Shiro?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.06,0:15:59.85,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Head down and into the central courtyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.27,0:16:06.02,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,As long as we defend the two exits, \Nwe can hold our position here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.52,0:16:08.78,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,We'll take turns recovering MP.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.78,0:16:11.03,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If we only had a safe zone...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.70,0:16:13.57,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The mob levels are high.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.99,0:16:15.82,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,This is tougher than I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.62,0:16:17.83,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.49,0:16:19.75,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,A minotaur!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.75,0:16:22.00,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Another set of two!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.00,0:16:24.00,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Six black ogres from above!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.00,0:16:25.79,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Twelve moon rabbits from above!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.79,0:16:27.25,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Split up and get ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.96,0:16:29.59,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No time to rest, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.59,0:16:32.17,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Raids are always like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.17,0:16:35.97,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Well, ever since I decided to go with \Nyou, I've been ready for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.97,0:16:38.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're always the one at the very front.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.01,0:16:42.02,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,You don't think I'm some kind \Nof bad luck charm, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.02,0:16:42.94,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,You'll make me cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.39,0:16:45.56,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make you cry later!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.56,0:16:46.86,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Serara!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.23,0:16:51.40,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Chief!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.40,0:16:53.07,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.32,0:16:54.78,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,No! Tohya!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.78,0:16:55.95,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I can't keep them delayed...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.57,0:16:59.12,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I'll use an Aura Heal—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.70,0:17:00.79,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.33,0:17:03.54,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,You can't just push an idol away—
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.54,0:17:05.50,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Tetra, heal everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.87,0:17:07.21,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Marielle!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.46,0:17:09.00,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Marielle!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.84,0:17:12.17,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,New enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.17,0:17:14.17,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Half-moon venom hydrangea.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.72,0:17:16.80,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe, we've lost three!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.80,0:17:18.30,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Our MP won't last.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.30,0:17:19.93,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm prioritizing Richou's group.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.93,0:17:21.64,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Hang in there somehow!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.64,0:17:22.93,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.60,0:17:25.06,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,AoE attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.06,0:17:26.56,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone split up!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.56,0:17:28.69,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,No, use the shrine priestess's four-way barrier!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.69,0:17:30.40,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,No one has the MP!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.74,0:17:35.95,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Korou!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.53,0:17:37.95,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Bad status...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.12,0:17:40.33,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Rot! DoT!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.33,0:17:42.33,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It's no good! Our HP won't last, either!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.62,0:17:44.66,Default,Li,0000,0000,0000,,Three lost. Five dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.66,0:17:46.79,Default,Li,0000,0000,0000,,We've lost a third in such a short time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.25,0:17:49.54,Default,Li,0000,0000,0000,,We can't keep going! This is really bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.54,0:17:50.71,Default,So,0000,0000,0000,,Shiro...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.71,0:17:51.96,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Give the order to withdraw!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.21,0:17:54.09,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Shiro!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.22,0:17:56.09,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,My lord...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.64,0:18:00.72,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Flip Gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.19,0:18:13.90,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Where are we? A studio?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.19,0:18:20.74,Location,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(401,1)\an9}Calling Fortress \NSafe Zone A\N{\fs18}Japan Server\NShibuya\NDungeon/ No Monsters\NNo PvP\NSkill Use Restricted\NEntry Restrictions/ None\NExit Restrictions/ None
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.90,0:18:17.99,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,So this is the revive point... \NNot the dungeon's entrance?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.49,0:18:20.74,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Marie, I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.74,0:18:22.49,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't protect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.49,0:18:24.12,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.12,0:18:27.50,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I just fell down the hole and ended up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.50,0:18:28.37,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Does it hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.37,0:18:29.67,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Want to see my panties?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.67,0:18:30.75,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.75,0:18:32.75,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It's only a scratch.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.05,0:18:36.34,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Um, thanks for your help back there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.17,0:18:38.84,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.84,0:18:41.89,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,You had more MP left than I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.89,0:18:43.26,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't even think about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.56,0:18:45.43,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Marielle!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.56,0:18:47.18,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't been on a raid this tough in a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.43,0:18:47.98,Default,M(Background),0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}That tickles!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.98,0:18:49.40,Default,N(Background),0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Hey, get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.10,0:18:50.27,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.56,0:18:52.44,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.57,0:18:54.48,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.20,0:18:59.78,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.62,0:19:05.79,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.84,0:19:15.05,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,H-Henrietta?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.34,0:19:16.38,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,My lord...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.56,0:19:27.56,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Um, Shiroe...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.02,0:19:31.15,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,We're staying in this world!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.40,0:19:33.73,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I know what you're thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.11,0:19:38.49,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,You're worried that if we destroy the antenna,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.49,0:19:40.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we won't be able to go home, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.40,0:19:45.53,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't that I don't want to go home, \Nbut I wasn't really sure about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.37,0:19:50.75,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,If I can have time to think it over, \Nthat's just as good.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.75,0:19:54.63,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't mean we'll never get home, does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.63,0:19:59.26,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,And we can't just leave the People of the Land.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.05,0:20:02.26,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,It didn't
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.43,0:20:06.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,go well for us in Safil...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.47,0:20:09.81,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Even if they thank us and say we saved them,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.81,0:20:11.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,some people will never make it home.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.23,0:20:15.23,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know if we'll be able to go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.23,0:20:18.53,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,But being able to go home makes you happy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.03,0:20:21.07,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,So we need to make everyone happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.99,0:20:24.07,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,We can go home after we do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.53,0:20:28.58,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,You lack resolve, guild master.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.87,0:20:32.08,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Just focus on what you can do!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.08,0:20:34.79,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.79,0:20:37.42,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,But I won't let you bear the burden alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.42,0:20:38.67,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,We...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.46,0:20:41.59,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I will bear it with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.84,0:20:42.93,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.89,0:20:46.10,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,You heard them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.43,0:20:48.10,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.10,0:20:48.89,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.64,0:20:51.10,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.73,0:20:54.56,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be fine, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.56,0:20:56.11,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Akatsuki...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.82,0:21:00.65,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.65,0:21:02.61,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you're safe?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.95,0:21:05.03,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We couldn't reach you with telepathy,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.03,0:21:07.03,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,so I got worried and came to look—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.03,0:21:07.87,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.53,0:21:10.37,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Someone's in front of the antenna.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.00,0:21:13.37,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I can't see his status from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.83,0:21:15.37,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But most likely...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.37,0:21:16.83,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.83,0:21:20.38,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Woodstock, you return to Akihabara \Nand bolster the defenses.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.71,0:21:22.01,Default,So,0000,0000,0000,,The raid boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.30,0:21:24.93,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,He wasn't there when we investigated, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.93,0:21:27.55,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he spawns when the moon rises?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.55,0:21:28.93,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Like the eternal moths?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.93,0:21:30.76,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,What a pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.47,0:21:33.81,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Which means if we defeat him...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.81,0:21:36.10,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,The moths might all disappear, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.35,0:21:39.02,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know if he'll be that easy to handle...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.02,0:21:42.07,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,But the weird parts of this are still a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.40,0:21:45.74,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Henrietta.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.74,0:21:47.32,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,You're welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.45,0:21:52.83,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Antenna... MP... Raid boss, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.08,0:21:54.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meow.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.67,0:22:00.21,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,There are thirty-four minutes until moonrise.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.21,0:22:01.34,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,There's no time—
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.34,0:22:03.17,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Thirty minutes is plenty.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.09,0:22:09.43,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,It was never possible to choose \Neither the world or the antenna.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.80,0:22:14.18,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Pick one? That's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.23,0:22:16.98,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,So we won't choose.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.98,0:22:19.98,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,We'll just tear apart this nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.52,0:22:22.86,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Let's save them both.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.86,0:22:24.49,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The world and the antenna.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.41,0:22:33.83,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show you what "two birds \Nwith one stone" really means.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.67,0:24:08.30,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The counterattack begins.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.30,0:24:10.63,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Shining glasses and sharpened minds.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.63,0:24:12.43,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Friends you can believe in.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.43,0:24:14.43,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,They won't pick just one anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.43,0:24:15.76,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,They'll protect everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.76,0:24:16.89,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,That is their answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.89,0:24:22.19,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,At the end of the battle, they reach a place \Nwhere Shiroe takes on a new quest.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.19,0:24:24.69,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,For the two worlds he loves so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.81,0:24:31.03,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,The Pioneers
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.11,0:24:27.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time: The Pioneers.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.15,0:24:28.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cross over the horizon.
